processDataMap

public static java.lang.Object[] processDataMap(java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.Object> map,
                                                java.lang.String flag,
                                                java.lang.String idCol,
                                                java.lang.String delim)
Utility method to put all fields in alphabetical order. It also filters out the ID column which is convenient in update statements unless the idCol passed is null By default, the idCol will be excluded if defined. If null then it will be included

Parameters:
map - the map containing the data
flag - the tag to match in order to parse data
idCol - the Id column tag to filter out. If null it will not be filtered.
delim - the delimiter to be used
Returns:
the processed map with alphabetical order keys

processDataMap

public static java.lang.Object[] processDataMap(java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.Object> map,
                                                java.lang.String flag,
                                                java.lang.String idCol,
                                                java.lang.String delim,
                                                java.lang.String row,
                                                boolean excludeIdCol,
                                                boolean putIdColLast)
Utility method to put all fields in alphabetical order. It also filters out the ID column which is convenient in update statements unless the idCol passed is null

Parameters:
map - the map containing the data
flag - the tag to match in order to parse data
idCol - the Id column tag to filter out. If null it will not be filtered out.
delim - the delimiter to be used
row - grabs for a specific row. Use null to ignore
excludeIdCol - if true then it will exclude the Id column value defined in idCol (if idCol = null it will include the value regardless)
putIdColLast - if true it will put the Id column value defined in idCol last (if idCol = null or excludeIdCol = true then this has no effect)
Returns:
the processed map with alphabetical order keys

viewSingleRowMapped

public static java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.Object> viewSingleRowMapped(DataResults rows)
Puts all data in a single row and appends the increasing number
e.g. row0_xxxxxx1, row0_xxxxxx2 etc. By default it will be prepended with row) and start the appending with 1

Parameters:
rows - the list of rows
firstAppendingNumber - the number to start the appending from (e.g. 1 then next will be 2 etc.)
Returns:
the list of rows with the field names prepended (with the same prepender) and appended (with increasing number)
